1)  Install Raspherry pi imager using sudo apt install rpi-imager
    Take sd card with reader and insert in pc
    Open imager and select sd card and Raspherry pi os lite 32 bit
    Press Str-Shift-X:
        Activate Hostname
        Activate SSH - Password
        Username: pi
        Password: RasPi
    Press Write
    Put SD card in Raspherry pi and activate power with ethernet connection online
    Run ssh pi@raspberrypi to connect

2)  sudo apt update
    sudo apt upgrade
    sudo apt install build-essential libtool-bin pkg-config autoconf automake texinfo flex bison libncurses-dev bc sshuttle libssl-dev git vim gcc-arm*
    git clone  https://github.com/openocd-org/openocd.git
    git checkout 9ea7f3d647c8ecf6b0f1424002dfc3f4504a162c
    
    In openocd repo:
        ./bootstrap
        ./configure --enable-bcm2835gpio
        make
        sudo make install
    openocd -f stm32f0raspberry.cfg
        Open On-Chip Debugger 0.12.0-01004-g9ea7f3d64 (2024-05-08-19:50)
